<p class="qtext_para" style="margin-bottom: 1em; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, Times, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; font-size: 15px;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;“ You will marry a person who has had years of life before he met you. He has been hurt , has failed , has struggled. He has scars. He won't be perfect.</p><p class="qtext_para" style="margin-bottom: 1em; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, Times, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; font-size: 15px;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;There will be so many days where he won’t be your&nbsp;<i>better</i>&nbsp;half, that’s when you be his. And when you aren’t his&nbsp;<i>better</i>&nbsp;half, he should be yours.</p><p class="qtext_para" style="margin-bottom: 1em; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, Times, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; font-size: 15px;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;And as you get to know more about him , you will learn things you may not like. He will grow and change, as will you. But understand that he too will learn things about you. He may not necessarily like them.</p><p class="qtext_para" style="margin-bottom: 1em; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, Times, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; font-size: 15px;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;As his wife , you should strive to grow together and learn to accept each other's flaws. Don't drop the pin at the first problem you run into. Don't run . Work things through. He's flawed as are you. Meet each other halfway.</p><p class="qtext_para" style="margin-bottom: 1em; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, Times, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; font-size: 15px;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ego has no place in a marriage. Comparison, too.</p><p class="qtext_para" style="margin-bottom: 1em; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, Times, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; font-size: 15px;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Marriage is a commitment, honor it with all your heart“</p><p class="qtext_para" style="margin-bottom: 1em; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, Times, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; font-size: 15px;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;This is what my father told me.</p><p class="qtext_para" style="margin-bottom: 1em; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, Times, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; font-size: 15px;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;It's so easy to say this but acting this through is very hard. Ask me, I know. I also think that this advice is gender neutral.</p><p class="qtext_para" style="margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, Times, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; font-size: 15px;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;All of us are flawed and scarred. Keeping our expectations in check will help immensely with marital life.</p><p class="qtext_para" style="margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, Times, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; font-size: 15px;"><br></p><p class="qtext_para" style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, Times, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; font-size: 15px;"><a href="https://www.quora.com/What-must-a-wife-know/answer/Saumya-George-3?srid=uLaia" target="_blank">Reference</a></p>
